      <!-- AI Stack Section -->
      <section class="section ai-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">AI & Machine Learning</h2>
          <i class="section-icon bx bx-brain"></i>
        </div>

        <p class="section-subtitle">Designing and building AI systems that are practical, ethical, and accessible in
          low-connectivity regions.</p>

        <div class="ai-grid">
          <div class="ai-card">
            <i class="bx bx-brain ai-icon"></i>
            <h3 class="ai-card-title">LLM Systems & Applied Deployment</h3>
            <p class="ai-card-desc">
              Hands-on experimentation with OpenAI, Mistral, LLaMA, and Ollama. Focused on lightweight inference,
              fine-tuning small models (SLMs), and running models locally on constrained hardware. Building AI that is
              usable beyond high-compute environments.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="ai-card">
            <i class="bx bx-wifi-off ai-icon"></i>
            <h3 class="ai-card-title">Offline-First AI Infrastructure</h3>
            <p class="ai-card-desc">
              Building systems based on the core idea that AI shouldn't require stable internet. Exploring SMS-based
              interactions, edge deployment, and low-bandwidth inference designed specifically for African realities
              (e.g., AANI).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="ai-card">
            <i class="bx bx-globe ai-icon"></i>
            <h3 class="ai-card-title">Ethical & Regional AI Exploration</h3>
            <p class="ai-card-desc">
              Actively exploring privacy-preserving architectures and regionally inclusive datasets. Questioning
              infrastructure assumptions and designing systems for the Global South, aiming to reduce dependency on
              Western cloud ecosystems.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="ai-card">
            <i class="bx bx-bulb ai-icon"></i>
            <h3 class="ai-card-title">AI Product & Strategy</h3>
            <p class="ai-card-desc">
              Thinking in terms of distribution and viability, not just models. Evaluating the cost of training vs.
              inference, comparing open vs. proprietary ecosystems, and framing products around safety, user experience,
              and scale.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>


